Glossary Alternating current (AC) - current that changes direction, your typical power outlet;
Direct Current (DC) - one way current used in most electronics;
Volts (v) - literally &ldquo;pressure&rdquo; of power;
Current (amperage) (I) - literally &ldquo;amount&rdquo; of power;
Resistance (Ohm) (r) - the relation property between voltage and current;
Components Resistor a piece of tubular material reisting n ohms. Resistance is measured in colour coded system of multiplied values and tolerance (accuracy).
